      "explanation": "虽然(suī rán) means 'although / even though' and 但是(dàn shì) means 'but / however'. They always appear together as a pair. Structure: 虽然(suī rán) + Clause 1, 但是(dàn shì) + Clause 2. The subject can appear before 虽然(suī rán) or after it. Note: In Chinese, 但是(dàn shì) must follow even though English can drop 'but'.",
